// v1.8 C3: the variant-generic check works for any user-declared
// sum-type schema, not just `Result`. Here `Pair<T, U>` has a
// `Both { left: T, right: U }` variant; the slot
// `Pair<Int, String>` flows `T -> Int, U -> String` into the
// constructor, so a swapped pair is rejected statically.
// EXPECTED: ≥ 1 × StaticTypeMismatch on the swapped value.
#schema Pair<T, U> Enum<Both { left: T, right: U }>
{ Pair<Int, String> p: Pair.Both { left: "wrong", right: 99 } }
